dN/dS ratios for missense and nonsense mutations acting on a set of genes in endometrial glands

Markdown file to present the methods to show dN/dS ratios for missense and nonsense mutations in endometrial glands. Before you start the following analyses, please convert the corresponding excel source data files to tab-delimited text files. The source data files are provided in our paper (Yamaguchi et al. Nat Commun in press).

Clean up workspace

rm(list=ls())

Load libraries

library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(tidyr)

Evaluate dN/dS ratios for missense and nonsense mutations acting on a set of genes

analysis_list <- c("all_genes", "cancer_gene_census", "pan_gynecologic_cancer_genes", "non_cancer_genes")
analysis_list2 <- c("All genes", "Cancer gene census (CGC)", "Pan-gynecologic cancer genes (Pan-gyn)", "Non cancer genes")
type_list <- c("missense", "nonsense")

dNdS_est <- function(a,b,c,d) {
  poi_dat <- data.frame(
    num_obs = c(a, b),
    num_exp = c(c, d),
    explan_var = c("w", "c"))
  res <- summary(glm(num_obs ~ offset(log(num_exp)) + explan_var, family="poisson", data=poi_dat))$coefficients
  value <- exp(res["explan_varw", "Estimate"])
  lower_95 <- exp(res["explan_varw", "Estimate"] - 1.96 * res["explan_varw", "Std. Error"])
  upper_95 <- exp(res["explan_varw", "Estimate"] + 1.96 * res["explan_varw", "Std. Error"])
  pvalue <- res["explan_varw", "Pr(>|z|)"]
  return(c(value, lower_95, upper_95, pvalue))
}
res_sum <- mapply(dNdS_est, dNdS_data$num_nonsynonymous_mut, dNdS_data$num_synonymous_mut, dNdS_data$num_nonsynonymous_mut_exp, dNdS_data$num_synonymous_mut_exp)
dNdS_data$dNdS_value <- res_sum[1, ]
dNdS_data$lower_95 <- res_sum[2, ]
dNdS_data$upper_95 <- res_sum[3, ]
dNdS_data$p_value <- res_sum[4, ]
# The result of this analysis is recorded in "source_data_13.txt".

Visualize dN/dS ratios for missense and nonsense mutations acting on a set of genes

dNdS_data$analysis2 <- factor(dNdS_data$analysis, 
  levels=c("all_genes", "cancer_gene_census", "pan_gynecologic_cancer_genes", "non_cancer_genes"))
labeli_categ <- as_labeller(c("missense" = "Missense", "nonsense" = "Nonsense"))

red <- rgb(196/255, 0/255, 38/255, 1)
blue <- rgb(26/255, 115/255, 186/255, 1)

p_dnds <- ggplot(dNdS_data, aes(x=analysis2, y=dNdS_value, fill=type))
p_dnds <- p_dnds + geom_errorbar(width=0.1, aes(ymin=lower_95, ymax=upper_95), colour="black")
p_dnds <- p_dnds + geom_point(shape=21, colour="black", size=5)
p_dnds <- p_dnds + facet_wrap(~ type, nrow=1, ncol=2, scales="free_y", labeller=labeli_categ)
p_dnds <- p_dnds + coord_trans(y="log")
p_dnds <- p_dnds + scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(0.5, 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32), limits=c(0.5, 32))
p_dnds <- p_dnds + scale_x_discrete(labels=c("All", "CGC", "Pan-gyn", "Non-can"))
p_dnds <- p_dnds + xlab("")
p_dnds <- p_dnds + ylab("dN/dS ratio")
p_dnds <- p_dnds + scale_fill_manual(values = c(red, blue))
p_dnds <- p_dnds + theme(
  legend.position="none",
  axis.line=element_line(colour="#d3d3d3"),
  panel.grid.major=element_line(colour="#d3d3d3"),
  panel.grid.minor=element_blank(),
  panel.border=element_blank(),
  panel.background=element_blank(),
  axis.ticks=element_blank(),
  axis.text.x=element_text(size=20, colour="black", angle=45, hjust=0.5, vjust=0.5),
  axis.text.y=element_text(size=20, colour="black"),
  axis.title=element_text(size=20),
  strip.text.x=element_text(size=20, colour="white"),
  strip.text.y=element_text(size=20),
  strip.background=element_rect(fill="black"))

plot(p_dnds)

Visualize dN and dS values for missense mutations acting on individual genes

gene_order1 <- c("KRAS", "PIK3CA", "PPP2R1A", "FBXW7", "PTEN", "PIK3R1", "FGFR2", "ARHGAP35", "PLXNB2")

dNdS_ind_miss <- select(dNdS_ind, -dN_nonsense)
dNdS_ind_miss2 <- filter(dNdS_ind_miss, gene %in% gene_order1)
dNdS_ind_long <- dNdS_ind_miss2 %>% gather(key="type", value="value", -gene, -role)
dNdS_ind_long$type <- sub("_missense", "", dNdS_ind_long$type)
dNdS_ind_long$gene2 <- factor(dNdS_ind_long$gene, levels=gene_order1)

p_mis <- ggplot(data=dNdS_ind_long, aes(x=gene2, y=value, fill=type))
p_mis <- p_mis + geom_bar(stat="identity", position="dodge", color="black")
p_mis <- p_mis + scale_fill_manual(values=c(red, "white"), name="")
p_mis <- p_mis + xlab("")
p_mis <- p_mis + ylab("Estimates of dN and dS")
p_mis <- p_mis + theme(
  axis.ticks=element_blank(),
  axis.text.x=element_text(size=20, colour="black", angle=45, vjust=1, hjust=1),
  axis.text.y=element_text(size=20, colour="black"),
  axis.title=element_text(size=20),
  legend.text=element_text(size=20),
  panel.grid.major=element_blank(),
  panel.border=element_blank(),
  panel.background=element_blank(),
  legend.position="top")

plot(p_mis)

Visualize distribution of dN - dS values for missense and nonsense mutations

dNdS_ind$dN_m <- dNdS_ind$dN_missense - dNdS_ind$dS
dNdS_ind$dN_n <- dNdS_ind$dN_nonsense - dNdS_ind$dS

p_dist <- ggplot(dNdS_ind, aes(x=dN_n, y=dN_m, fill=role))
